> Hi,
> 
> On Sun, 22 Aug 1999, Guest section DW wrote:
> 
> > Sooner or later we'll need a new bootloader.
> 
> Why don't you try GRUB? It's free, and it already can load Linux, but it's
> native environment is more performant - it can load any size image, it
> works in protected mode, easily configurable, a lot more user friendly
> than LILO, and it can load the image file even from fat filesystem.
> Plus it can supply the kernel with lots of usable information (the boot
> device, parameters, and the memory size [even over 64Mb]). I say you
> should give it a try.
> 
http://www.uruk.org/grub
